request.description:
To be used by Admin to get a SPECIFIC user. Can only be accesed by admins, must send the AUTH with access token. Idea is that admin first uses normal get/search for users, and uses this to get all the details of the account.

The request should be sent to {{baseUrl}}admin/admin_users with a payload containing the "username" parameter.

### Response

The response for this request can be documented as a JSON schema as follows:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "user": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "id": {"type": "integer"},
                "username": {"type": "string"},
                "password": {"type": "string"},
                "salt": {"type": "string"},
                "firstName": {"type": ["string", "null"]},
                "lastName": {"type": ["string", "null"]},
                "email": {"type": "string"},
                "avatar": {"type": ["string", "null"]},
                "phoneNumber": {"type": ["string", "null"]},
                "role": {"type": "string"},
                "deleted": {"type": "boolean"},
                "createdAt": {"type": "string"},
                "updatedAt": {"type": "string"}
            },
            "required": ["id", "username", "password", "salt", "email", "role", "deleted", "createdAt", "updatedAt"]
        }
    }
}

 ```

